Pure-TS port of MPFR's mpfr_const_euler_bs_init (mpfr/src/const_euler.c L51-L60). Initialises a binary-splitting state struct used by the Euler-Mascheroni constant computation. The struct (mpfr/src/const_euler.c L39-L49) is a 6-tuple of mpz_t fields:

  struct mpfr_const_euler_bs_struct {
    mpz_t P; mpz_t Q; mpz_t T;
    mpz_t C; mpz_t D; mpz_t V;
  };

The C function calls mpz_init on each of the six -- creating six zero-valued GMP integers.

The TS port returns a fresh object {P: 0n, Q: 0n, T: 0n, C: 0n, D: 0n, V: 0n}. BigInt has no separate 'init' phase; literal 0n is a zero-valued bigint.

This function is an INTERNAL helper, not part of the public mpfr_const_euler API. It exists to support binary-splitting recursion in the Euler-constant cache.

Class 'misc'. No-arg function -- single output. Rule 7 minimums carved out per buildopt_float128_p precedent.
